#Text=In-Young Ahn
#Text=The native form of this personal name is Ahn In-Young .
#Text=This article uses Western name order when mentioning individuals .
#Text=In-Young Ahn
#Text=is a South Korean scientist .
#Text=She is known for being the first South Korean woman to visit Antarctica and the first Asian woman to become an Antarctic station leader ( King Sejong Station ) . [ 2 ] [ 3 ] [ 4 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=She is a benthic ecologist and is currently working as a principal research scientist for Korea Polar Research Institute . [ 6 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=Early life and education

#Text=Ahn graduated from Seoul National University in 1982 ( majoring in Biological Oceanography ) and then received her PhD in Coastal Oceanography from the State University of New York at Stony Brook in 1990 .
#Text=Ahn started her research at the Korean Polar Research Institute ( KOPRI ) on July 1 , 1991 . [ 3 ]
#Text=Career and impact

#Text=Ahn was in charge of environmental monitoring program at the King Sejong Station from 1996 to 2011 , and conducted field surveys to obtain scientific data necessary for designation of the Antarctic Specially Protected Area ( ASPA #171 ) near the Korean station .

#Text=Ahn has also served as a representative and a National Contact Point of the Committee for Environmental Protection ( CEP ) at the Antarctic Treaty Consultative Meetings from 1997 through 2014 , until she was designated as the overwintering officer-in-charge . [ 8 ]
#Text=Ahn served as the vice president of the Korea Polar Research Institute ( KOPRI ) from May 2010 to June 2012 .
#Text=She also served as Vice President of the Korean Society of Oceanography in 2010 – 2011 , [ 9 ] and Korea Federation of Women 's Science & Technology Associations in 2014 and 2015 . [ 10 ]
#Text=She was expedition leader of the 28th overwintering team ( 2015 ) of the South Korean King Sejong Antarctic station , where she served as the station chief for about a year . [ 6 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=Ahn 's research interests include Antarctic marine benthic ecology with special interests on benthic invertebrates and monitoring on Antarctic coastal marine ecosystems . [ 3 ]
#Text=She has studied the Antarctic clam Laternula elliptica , a dominant marine bivalve around Antarctic Continent .
#Text=Ahn 's current research includes studies on the impacts of glacier retreat on nearshore marine benthic communities around the King Sejong Station .

#Text=She is currently an adjunct professor at the University of Science & Technology ( UST ) , and a principal research scientist at the Korean Polar Institute ( KOPRI ) , which forms part of Korea Institute of Ocean Science & Technology ( KIOST ) .
#Text=Awards and honors
#Text=The South Korean government awarded Ahn a Medal of Science & Technology Merit for outstanding accomplishment in Antarctic Research in April 2001 . [ 11 ]

#Text=She was further awarded a Commendation from the South Korean Ministry of Environment in June 2008 for her contribution in the designation of Antarctic Specially Protected Area ( ASPA #171 ) near the King Sejong station . [ 12 ]
#Text=In 2016 , she additionally received South Korea 's Prime Minister 's award in recognition of her achievement as the station leader at King Sejong station . [ 13 ]
#Text=Selected works
#Text=Ahn , In-Young , et al.
